<dl id="n08107p"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08107p">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08107p"> 107(p)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> 4M (Sons&apos; Rest) in bed / compose opera </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: 4M was an early sign for the four old men. See <a name="n01028f" href="n01all.htm#n01028f">N01 (VI.B.10):028(f)</a>: &lsquo;The Sons&apos; Rest / (Cunniam).&rsquo; It seems here to be connected with Captain Thomas Cunniam, a publican and friend of John S. Joyce, possibly as the name of one of his pubs. See also 109(g).</mm> </dd></dl>
